      • knapsackSum

        public static int knapsackSum(int[] w,
                              int n,
                              int limit)
        Knapsack recursion for part A.

        Find sum of the greatest combination of numbers that are under a given limit

        Parameters:
        w - int array that contains n positive integers (n <= w.length).
        n - points to the position in the array
        limit - numerical limit for the sum
        Returns:
        the sum of some of these integers such that it has the largest possible value without exceeding limit.

      • knapsackSum

        public static int knapsackSum(int[] w,
                              int n,
                              int limit,
                              java.util.List<java.lang.Integer> list)
        Knapsack recursion for part B.

        Find sum of the greatest combination of numbers that are under a given limit, and create a list of the combination of integers.

        Parameters:
        w - int array that contains n positive integers (n <= w.length).
        n - points to the position in the array
        limit - numerical limit for the sum
        list - List object to track which numbers in w have been added to the sum
        Returns:
        the sum of some of these integers such that it has the largest possible value without exceeding limit.
